ARE WE FREE YET?

Colonial powers made many victims in the past. These crimes have lingering consequences such as underdevelopment, inequality and national divides.
This table shows groups of colonial empires. Countries are arranged by their most frequent score in Civil Liberties and Political Rights
from 1995 till 2020. Scores go from 1 (most free) to 7 (least free). Furthermore the period of colonial rule is shown in bars.
Time under colonial rule is in red, while the total span of time as ruler is gray. The scales of the bars are different for each group

Freedom scores data: Freedom House and the United Nations by way of Arthur Cheib | Colonial rule data: Wikipedia | Table by: Ícaro Bernardes - @IcaroBSC
